Aim:- Write a Program to Implement Control flow Statments and Looping State

Algorithm:-

Step:1.	Start
Step:2.	Initialize runs, balls, wickets, runs conceded, overs, and catches.
Step:3.	Calculate strike rate using sr = (runs / balls) × 100.
Step:4.	Calculate economy rate using eco = runs_conceded / overs.
Step:5.	Determine batting performance using runs and strike rate conditions.
Step:6.	Determine bowling performance using wickets and economy rate conditions.
Step:7.	Determine fielding performance using number of catches.
Step:8.	Evaluate overall performance based on batting and bowling results.
Step:9.	Display batting, bowling, fielding, and overall result.
Step:10. Stop.



Code:- #Contol Statements and Looping Statements 


runs = 148
balls = 50
wickets = 4
runs_conceded = 29
overs = 2
catches = 3

sr = (runs / balls) * 100
eco = runs_conceded / overs

if runs >= 50 and sr >= 120:
    bat = "Excellent"
elif runs >= 36 and sr >= 100:
    bat = "Good"
elif runs >= 20:
    bat = "Average"
else:
    bat = "Poor"

if wickets >= 3 and eco <= 6:
    bowl = "Excellent"
elif wickets >= 2 and eco <= 8:
    bowl = "Good"
elif wickets >= 1:
    bowl = "Average"
else:
    bowl = "Poor"

if catches >= 2:
    field = "Outstanding"
elif catches == 1:
    field = "Active"
else:
    field = "Need Improvement"

if bat == "Excellent" and bowl == "Excellent":
    result = "Star All Rounder"
elif bat == "Good" and bowl == "Good":
    result = "Strong All Rounder"
elif bat == "Good" or bowl == "Good":
    result = "Supporting All Rounder"
else:
    result = "Needs Improvement"

print("Batting Performance:", bat)
print("Bowling Performance:", bowl)
print("Fielding Performance:", field)
print("Overall Result:", result)


Output:-
Batting Performance: Excellent
Bowling Performance: Average
Fielding Performance: Outstanding
Overall Result: Needs Improvement
